Lab2, Wendy Chen
10/2016

Durable on-disk graph store.

The durable disk used is: /dev/sdb
Flag for formatting disk: -f
Flag for randomizing/erasing disk: -r

Make sure permissions of /dev/sdb are readable and writable.

Invoke server:
$ ./cs426_graph_server -f <port> <devfile>
or
$ ./cs426_graph_server <port> <devfile>

Example:
./cs426_graph_server -f 8000 /dev/sdb
./cs426_graph_server -r 8000 /dev/sdb

New request command: checkpoint
ie. curl -H "Content-Type: application/json" -X POST -d '' http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/checkpoint


The test script demonstrates that the logging works over multiple blocks.
To test durability, stop the server and restart.  Query the graph to see it exists still.

